According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Precipitated Silica from Rice Husk Ash market was valued at USD 552 million in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 608 million in 2026 to USD 1.01 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 10.4% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing strong momentum as industries increasingly adopt sustainable and bio-based materials to reduce environmental impact while improving product performance. Produced by extracting high-purity silica from rice husk ash—an agricultural byproduct—precipitated silica offers an eco-friendly alternative to conventional silica and is widely used in tires, industrial rubber, coatings, plastics, personal care products, and specialty applications.
